# =============================================================================
# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE suppressions (false positives / accepted risks)
# =============================================================================
#
# FORMAT
# ──────
# One CVE-ID per line.  Lines starting with '#' are comments.
# Each active suppression MUST document:
#   • Why the CVE is not exploitable or acceptable in this context
#   • Who reviewed it and on what date
#   • When the decision should be revisited
#
# GOVERNANCE
# ──────────
# This file is version-controlled and reviewed at every base image update.
# Adding an entry here is a deliberate security decision, not a quick fix.
# Prefer updating the base image or a dependency over adding suppressions.
#
# EXAMPLE FORMAT (do not uncomment without a real review)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2023-36617
# ^ urllib ReDoS — only triggered by malformed URLs from untrusted input.
#   This app does not accept user-supplied URLs.
#   Reviewed: Alice, 2024-06-01 | Revisit: next base image bump.
#
# CVE-2023-29383
# ^ shadow-utils — requires local shell access to exploit.
#   Container runs as non-root; no shell exposed to untrusted users.
#   Reviewed: Bob, 2024-06-15 | Revisit: Q3 2024.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Active suppressions (add below after security review):

CVE-2026-42496
^ perl-archive-tar path traversal via crafted symlinks.
  Affects perl-base shipped in Debian 13.5 base image.
  No exploit path in this container: application does not process untrusted archives or symlinks.
  No fixed version available in current Debian repositories at time of review.
  Reviewed: Lab author, 2026-06-24 | Revisit: next base image update.

CVE-2026-8376
^ Perl heap buffer overflow during compilation of specific constructs.
  Affects perl-base in Debian 13.5 slim image.
  Container does not execute untrusted Perl code or compile external Perl modules at runtime.
  No upstream patched package available at time of review.
  Reviewed: Lab author, 2026-06-24 | Revisit: next base image update.